On Sun, 3 Nov 2002, Bob in Houston wrote:

> FWIW........
> Given that, it would appear that MB feels 230 degrees F is a monitor point
> to start cooling down on engine oil, and at 257 degrees F, it is an oil
> temp value that needs more cooling attention.
>
> Of course, we are talking 8.5 Qts of oil in the gut as opposed to our bus
> capacity of 3 Qts.

Since we are talking about a continuous flow of heat, the amount of oil
does not make much difference.  The only thing that a large oil capacity
does is slow down the warmup a bit.  It won't change the ultimate
temperatures.

George Lyle
